```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.androidautomationsof">

    <!-- 
        This AndroidManifest.xml file defines the fundamental information about the 
        Android automation software, "Android Automation Tool". The features 
        include an easy-to-use graphical interface and strong automation capabilities.
    -->

    <!-- 
        This permission allows the application to access the internet, ensuring 
        that the automation processes can operate 24/7 by communicating with 
        external social media platforms for scheduled tasks.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    
    <!-- 
        This permission enables the application to save data locally as needed. 
        It supports functionalities such as storing user settings and logs, 
        enhancing the user experience.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    
    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to read data from external storage. 
        It is crucial for accessing and managing media files for automation tasks.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <!-- 
        The following settings define the applicationâ€™s metadata and components 
        for registration and execution.
    -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">

        <!-- 
            MainActivity serves as the entry point for the application, providing 
            the user interface and enabling users to configure automation tasks 
            without the need for coding.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            AutomationService is a background service that handles the automation 
            tasks in 24/7 operation mode. It runs continuously to ensure that 
            scheduled operations for platforms like Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok 
            are executed without interruption.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService"
                 android:enabled="true"
                 android:exported="false" />
        
    </application>

</manifest>
```

### Explanation:

- **Permissions**: The manifest declares necessary permissions, enabling internet access for automation and storage access for data management. Each permission comment emphasizes its capability in supporting automation features.
  
- **Components**: The `MainActivity` serves as the user interface for configuration, while `AutomationService` allows for continuous operations, highlighting MadHub's robust automation characteristics.

- **Feature-First Comments**: Comments are oriented towards explaining features first and then detailing how configurations support those features, aligning with the specified writing style.
